      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "This preface gives a lively picture of the intense, universal interest felt by the early Church in the story of the Lord Jesus: Apostles constantly telling what they had seen and heard; many of their hearers taking notes of what they said for the benefit of tnemselves and others: through these gospelets acquaintance with the evangelic history circulating among believers, creating a thirst for more and yet more; imposing on such a man as Luke the task of preparing a Gospel as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "full, correct",
